=80=9D. The mind then rejoices at its success, and hardens its belief syste=
m.

7.       Under such indoctrinated or polarized or biased mind system, t=
he reality will manifest, according to the belief of the mind.

8.       On=
ce this belief hardens, the mind keeps hell bent to propagate it. And this =
becomes propaganda. In Sanskruta we call it Vimoodha or Moodha meaning a mi=
nd becoming hardened to such an extent, that it blocks all intellectual gat=
eways, that is, it completely silences Buddhi or intellect or capacity to t=
hink logically and neutrally without any bias.

9.       This is basically =
a sick mind for which there is a special treatment ordained by the divine, =
where all sick mind goes for treatment for permanent cure. There is a place=
 called hell administered by Yama Dharma-Raaja where all kinds of psycho-sp=
iritual treatment is given in a unique way for the upliftment of the sick s=
ouls.

10.   The company of wise people is the only tonic for sick minds. T=
he wise people have enhanced spiritual energy surrounding their body, which=
 is also called Grace-Light. This Grace-Light is very powerful and it can p=
ierce any hardened layer of sick mind, and awaken the dead or sleeping inte=
llect, and enlighten it.

11.   Once the sleeping intellect is awakened, th=
en that intellect will nourish the sick mind to the appropriate path, thus =
saving it from going to the mental hospital called hell.

12.   Saadhu Sang=
ati Parama Durlabha, meaning the company of wise is a very rare gift. When =
God is pleased with us, he blesses us with the company of wise. Wise men ar=
e verily the temple of God, for, in their heart resides The God.

13.   Shr=
i Krishna Himself says in Bhaagavatam, that he runs behind such wise people=
, so that the dust of their feet can fall on him and make him blessed.

14.=
   Shri MahaaVishnu is a Bhakta Vatsala, meaning caring and loving to devot=
ees, and a Braahmana Priya, meaning a lover and seeker of wise people.

15.=
   Let us prostrate before our Beloved Naaraayana to forgive us, and keep b=
lessing us with the Grace-Light in the form of company of wise.

